1. Car Insurance Class Diagram
This diagram defines the classes needed for a vehicle insurance domain, detailing the relationships between the Car, Owner, Insurance, Insurer, and the CarDatabase.

2. ATM Processing Class Diagram
This diagram maps out user interactions within a banking and transaction application. It uses inheritance to separate Admin and Client roles from a base User class. It also links clients to Account and Transaction processing.

3. Medical Clinic Class Diagram
This structure organizes clinic staff using an Employee interface. It models how Doctor, Nurse, and Secretary classes interact with Patient and Appointment objects, as well as a central Database.
